section.section:
With the advice and consent of the Senate, the Governor shall appoint 8 members who represent one or more of the following:
Municipal government;
County government;
A sanitary or a metropolitan commission;
Waterworks supervision;
Wastewater works or industrial wastewater works supervision;
Agriculture;
Industrial wastewater works superintendents; and
The Maryland Environmental Service.

The terms of members are staggered as required by the terms provided for members of the Board on July 1, 1981. The terms of those members end as follows:
Three in 1982;
One in 1983;
One in 1984; and
Two in 1985.
